column31: Friends, raise your hand if you can all use some EXTRA emotional support right about now! I know I can 🙋‍♀️ Let's talk about how essential oils impact our thoughts, traumas, beliefs and stuck emotions! To do this, we need to understand a little bit about how our brains work. Within your brain is something called the limbic system. This is referred to as the emotional center of your brain, because literally every thought, emotion, conscious and unconscious memory, knee-jerk reaction, personality trait, feeling of stress, or life lesson you’ve ever experienced, is thought to be held here, in your limbic system. It’s like a storage unit, and one of its jobs is to help you to process current situations in the tiniest fraction of a second to help you to determine, based on past situations, what is the best or safest way for you to think, feel, or react now? This is a self-preservation mechanism, basically to ensure that you are playing it safe, hanging out in your comfort zone and that no harm is going to come to you. All this information is stored in a way that keeps it pretty inaccessible to you as well, which is why it’s so frustrating when we’re trying to change these things, and we feel like we can’t do it. Think of your thoughts and emotions like wagon wheels, just traveling the same pathways over and over until they create these really deep ruts. ☸ We literally get stuck in these thought or emotional patterns, these ruts in our mind, and it can feel really impossible to get out of. Now, also within your limbic system is something called your olfactory bulb. This is literally your sense of smell. The olfactory bulb transmits smell information from the nose to the brain, and is thus necessary for a proper sense of smell. As a neural circuit, the olfactory bulb has one source of sensory input, and one output. And this is really unique because it’s the only one of your senses that’s processed in this part of your brain, right alongside your thoughts and emotions. Your olfactory bulb relays information directly into your limbic system. But it’s not just relaying smells. It’s actually relaying the things associated with smell. This is because your olfactory neurons themselves are capable of learning and remembering information, and they’re constantly undergoing something called neurogenesis, meaning they’re constantly renewing. Every six to 10 weeks, they are brand new neurons, ready to take in new information, and relay that to your limbic system as new messages. By the way, researchers are actually finding these olfactory neurons all over our body. Did you know your liver can actually smell what’s going through it? Let’s shift gears and talk about the oils for a minute. Pure essential oils are made up of natural and aromatic compounds. Most people understand how they work physically on the body. Lavender & Frankincense soothes and calms irritated skin, thyme oil supports balanced progesterone and peppermint supports digestion, and teal tree oil support deep healing of wounds. Just as these oils work with different systems of the body, the aromatic compounds are also working within the systems of your brain. Working through that olfactory bulb, some oils are going to calm certain areas of the limbic system. Others are going to stimulate. It can bring up memories, they can help us process trauma, they can increase confidence and courage, all by interacting with the limbic system, either by themselves or, this is where it gets juicy when you’re using them with other practices. They are work horses. + you hear the soft sound of rippling of the moving water when it's on + you get to humidify and clean the air + you breathe nanoparticles of the health OPTIMIZING oils + it comes with a remote + it plays soft chimes + it constructed with a glass dome and wood base + it has run time settings, so you can program and it can run for up to 12 hours. column31: Sadly, more and more reports are coming out of people of all ages, in all health circumstances, dying suddenly after the COVID-19 vaccines. The alarming rash of sudden deaths is coming after we were warned that elderly people may ‘coincidentally die after the shot, and that we should not be alarmed’ because old people just die…or something like that (read the concerning quote linked in website)–but what about a young person? Should we also expect young people to just die after the shot? Wouldn’t that mean the vaccine may be a problem?? It was bad when they told us to ignore deaths in the elderly (I thought this was the reason we were vaccinating–to prevent deaths) but it’s worse when we are being expected to ignore deaths in the young too. At what point do we stop everything and say: THIS IS NOT OK. Where are we going to draw the line? Back in 1976, the United States suspended its swine flu vaccine campaign after just 10 weeks: 40 people died suddenly (many of them elderly) and several hundred reports of Guillain Barre syndrome. They took the vaccine off the market. We are way past those numbers today. According to the CDC, VAERS has received 934 death reports after the COVID vaccines, as well as several hundred reports of anaphylaxis and facial paralysis. The Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System was estimated to only gather 1% of adverse events, as the majority of people, and even health care workers fail to connect the dots between vaccine and subsequent reaction. column31: Friends, I've been talking about hormones lately (because they regulate everything in the mind and body), have you heard of endocrine disrupting chemicals (EDCs) like BPA and Phthalates? These chemicals have hormone disrupting effects because of a concept known as hormone mimicry. In short, it’s when chemicals mimic the effects of hormones. This is especially problematic because they can bind to hormone receptors, blocking other hormones from being bound as they normally would and disrupting our delicate balance of hormones. Bisphenol A (BPA), which is most commonly thought to be in plastic but is also used in food cans (as the inner coating), feminine hygiene products, receipts and even children’s toys and clothing, has an estrogenic effect on the body- in other words, BPA can mimic estrogen and bind to estrogen receptors, blocking other hormones from being bound. This is why BPA can contribute to endocrine disorders including but not limited to infertility, PCOS and breast and prostate cancer. The dangers of BPA have become pretty mainstream, which is probably why you’ve now noticed so many “BPA-free” options in stores. Unfortunately, these aren’t any better as they’ve simply been replaced with chemicals (namely BPS and BPF) that have been shown to have virtually identical hormone disrupting effects as BPA. So, how can you reduce your exposure to these hormone disrupting chemicals? The key is avoiding repeated, daily exposure as that is how these toxins accumulate and do so in our FAT TISSUES and implement detoxification daily - even in small ways! ✔️Reduce consumption of canned food and packaged food ✔️Use glass and stainless steel instead of plastic (for food storage, water bottles and especially for cooking as chemicals are more likely to leach into the food) ✔️Decline paper receipts! (100% of people who handled receipts had BPA detected in their urine. (Erlich, et all. 2014, JAMA) ✔️Never heat up food in plastic or store hot food in plastic ✔️Purchase wooden toys for kids over plastic ones ✔️ Reduce chemicals in general, use non-toxic cleaners, clean self-care products, avoid "fragranced" items, avoid candles and swap out for pure essential oils. column31: *** The Heart of America *** . Today, Deb and I went to our local grocery store called: H.E.B. . We wanted to pick up a few things before the next snowstorm and historically, crazy weather we are getting near Austin, Texas. . Halfway through our shopping the stores power went out. It was still light out as it was only about 3:30pm. We kept shopping as hundreds of other people were too. I told Deb let’s hurry in case they tell us we must stop shopping and check out right away. We were picking up some milk and other items for other family members too and wanted to be sure we got everything we went there for. . Sure enough, about 10-15 minutes later one of the HEB employees asked us to head to the check out area and said: “we’ll check everyone out as quickly as we can as we have a process for these kinds of things”. . We got to a line with about 10 full carts in front of us and there were many other lines to both sides of us and many people behind us – probably several hundred people waiting to be checked out. BTW: the store had lots of empty shelves already but there was still enough stuff for most people’s needs. . We waited in line for about 15-20 minutes and barely moved up 1-2 slots. Then all of a sudden we started moving faster. We both thought: Wow, they are checking out people quickly. Must be all hands on deck. . In a few minutes, we were asked to move to the next checkout aisle that was open. We got to the checkout woman and she asked: “Do you have any alcohol?” I said: “No, but if you are giving out drinks, I could use one about now” 😊 . She then said: “Please go ahead but we can’t bag anything up for you.” At first, Deb and I were a bit confused and I asked: “How or who do we pay for our groceries?” We probably had a couple of hundred dollars worth of groceries. She said: “Just go ahead and be safe driving home.” Then we noticed the lines of people after the checkout stands proceeding with full carts of groceries all being directed out the store with many employees there to greet us on our way out. . Deb began tearing up which always gets me teared up too - as we could not believe the generosity of H.E.B. and the kindness of that wonderful gesture. They could just as easily asked us all to leave the store as soon as the power went out and asked us to just leave the groceries in the carts. But instead, they allowed people to continue to shop for another 10-15 minutes after the power went out and then let everyone leave the store without so much as a single dollar being asked for from the hundreds of people leaving the store. . This is the America that I know. Despite all the negative we hear/see being reported daily in the news. America and most Americans are still kind, thoughtful, generous, and caring. . I salute H.E.B. for the kindness they showed us, the thoughtfulness they showed us, the generosity they showed us, and the caring that they showed us (along with the other hundreds of fellow Texans in the store at that time). . From the bottom of mine and Deb’s heart, we will never forget what you did when no one would have blamed you for taking a different action and when no one expected such a wonderful gesture. . --- With Love Always and Grateful that America is Still the Land I Love, Tim H. P.S. On the way out the door, I turned to the HEB employees and said: "Oh wait...I forgot the Filet Mignon!" We all got a good laugh out of that one. 🙂 — with Lauren Angela.

column31: There is nothing on this earth that is 100% safe for all people, in all situations. This absolutely goes for herbs. There are herbs, or blends, that should not be used by very young children, or pregnant women, or various other groups. And there are even more herbs that, while not harmful, would not provide benefit to certain people or in certain situations. For example, nettle leaf is a great nutritive herb that is safe for just about everyone, but it can lead to allergic reactions in some, and it's not going to do anything for pain. It’s also naturally high in vitamin K1, which makes it not the best option for those who are concerned about blood clotting too much. It's only logical that all people are different. That their needs vary, and that there is nothing universal that works to benefit them. Which is why it's also fully logical that not everyone can benefit from every v@xcyne. Some will have reactions or injuries. Some will simply not need it because they are at low risk of illness and it doesn't provide much, if any, benefit to them. If we're being honest, we have to understand that *no* health intervention -- NONE -- is universally beneficial. That's the *rational* position. Why are there so many people who *irrationally* deny that and insist that v@xcynes actually are universally beneficial?

column31: Let's suppose that drugs, as designed, are actually perfectly safe. (Though they're not.) 90% of all drugs are generic. A drug can be approved for use as a generic if tests shows it is metabolized by the body at the same rate as the drug that is being copied. No other safety tests are required, even if "inactive" ingredients differ. Most of these generic drugs are made in India or China. The GMP standards and tracking are much more lax than in the US. The FDA is supposed to oversee these facilities, but they don't really have the manpower to do it. When they do tour facilities, they usually give weeks of advance notice. Several facilities have been caught purposely hiding or manipulating data to make it seem like the drugs they are producing meet safety and purity standards when they don't. Some have been found with filthy conditions. How many are doing these things...and aren't caught? Less than 1% of all drugs manufactured in China are actually tested for safety or purity once they reach US soil. There have been several massive recalls due to contamination in recent years. So I ask you again...how safe are these drugs, really?

column31: Sleep debt is the difference between the amount of sleep you need and the amount you actually get. For example, if you lose 2 hours of sleep each night, you'll have a sleep debt of 14 hours after a week. column31: Safe and effective has become a slogan to assuage fears, however, there is ample precedent that drugs once declared “safe and effective” can be anything but…safe and effective: Thalidomide was a sedative developed in 1953 used to treat morning sickness during pregnancy in the 1950s and the early 1960s. It was licensed in 46 countries, but not the US. In 1961, two doctors saw an association between the use of thalidomide use in expecting mothers and congenital malformations. Once publicized, more than 10,000 children around the globe were thought to have been born with the malformation as a result of thalidomide use. In addition to these abnormalities, there was an increase in the number of miscarriages reported by women during the same period of time. It was withdrawn from use in 1961. +++ Diethylstilbestrol (DES) is a "synthetic estrogen." During 1938-1971, U.S. physicians prescribed DES to pregnant women to prevent miscarriages and avoid other pregnancy problems. As a result, an estimated 5-10 million pregnant women and the children born of these pregnancies were exposed to DES. At the time, physicians thought DES was safe and would prevent miscarriages and pre-term (early) births. In 1953, research showed that DES did not prevent miscarriages or premature births, but was continued to be prescribed until 1971, when the FDA added a warning based on a 1971 that identified DES as a cause of a rare vaginal cancer in girls and young women who had been exposed to DES before birth (in the womb). DES daughters had about 40 times the risk of developing clear cell adenocarcinoma of the lower genital tract than unexposed women. +++ Primodos was a hormone-based pregnancy test used from 1958 and 1978 that consisted of two pills that contained synthetic hormones. It would induce menstruation in women who were not pregnant, absence of bleeding meant you were pregnant. In the 1960s research showed a link between the use of the drug and severe birth defects, and then in the 1970s it was concluded the product should not be used by pregnant women. It was finally withdrawn from use in 1978. 👉🏼 https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/drug-recalls-not-so-safe-after-all/

column31: Aching, tingling, itching and throbbing have all been used to describe the feeling of restless leg syndrome. This sensation seems to get worse at night. It can even disrupt sleep. There are several causes of RLS. However, it seems to affect women more than men. Pregnancy and nutrient deficiencies can also increase the risk. Is RLS something you deal with? If so, what do you do to help relieve the symptoms?

column31: People spend more time worrying about us, and not the *actual* criminals. 🤔🤡 “In the early 1990s, Pfizer was embroiled in a controversy about scores of fatalities linked to heart valves produced by its Shiley division. In 1992 it agreed to pay up to $205 million to settle thousands of lawsuits. In 1994 the company agreed to pay $10.75 million to settle Justice Department charges that it lied to regulators in seeking approval for the valves. In 2005 Pfizer had to stop advertising its arthritis medication Celebrex after a study showed that high doses were associated with an increased risk of heart attacks. Pfizer’s claims about the safety of the drug were further undermined when it came to light that the company had conducted a clinical trial back in 1999 that also pointed to the cardiac risk but which Pfizer kept secret. Pfizer, which was a pioneer in the once controversial practice of advertising pharmaceuticals, has frequently been accused of making false or misleading claims about its products. It has paid millions of dollars to resolve state and federal allegations about these practices. It has paid even larger amounts in cases involving allegations that the company promoted its drugs for uses not approved by the Food and Drug Administration. These include a $2.3 billion settlement in 2009 that covered criminal as well as civil allegations. Pfizer’s subsidiary Wyeth settled its own criminal-civil illegal marketing case for $490 million four years later. In 2016 Wyeth paid another $784 million to settle allegations that it reported false pricing information to the federal government.” https://www.corp-research.org/pfizer

column31: The other day a mom commented her 'children were fully vaccinated and very healthy, the oldest was a teen'. I replied ’That’s awesome, can I ask if they ever as babies or toddlers had ear infections, RSV, croup, bronchiolitis, pneumonia, wheeze, strep throat, diarrhea, eczema or if they have food allergies, etc. Any antibiotics prescribed in the first couple years, or ever?” And then I lost where the thread was! But I genuinely want to know the answer. We should all talk about this! This is NOT to shame anyone. If you support vaccinations, that is awesome. Let’s try to understand each other better. Do you have fully vaccinated kids? Do you have partially vaccinated, or unvaccinated kids?—How is their health? I can only speak from my experience, my kids are unvaccinated. My kids had a cold here and there, but nothing serious. I remember the first time we got called in a prescription. My son was 20 months old, he had a little rash on his back near his diaper, it was diagnosed ‘granuloma annulare’ and I think it was from the chemicals in the diaper. Anyways, his pediatrician went to order our ointment and his eyes got real big--we had no pharmacy attached to our account. We had never had a prescription! No antibiotics, no steroids, no acid reflux medications—nothing at all!! A few years later the same thing happened again when we did an intake at an ENT appt. for my daughter. Around 2 we found a little midline cyst on her neck and wanted to know more. The ENT intake asked all her questions: ear tubes? No. Asthma? no. Ear infections? No. Strep throat, pneumonia, Etc etc. We said no to EVERYTHING. The lady’s face lit up and said “Good Job Mom!!” My daughter got her very first ear infection last year at almost 5 years old. Each have had antibiotics once! Our only ER visit was for an eyebrow cut. #breastfeeding #unvaccinated What is your experience?

column31: Antacids are used to treat symptoms caused by too much stomach acid such as heartburn, upset stomach, or indigestion. They work to lower the amount of acid in the stomach. However, taking too much overtime can lead to a plethora of health issues. Stomach acid is important to our overall health, as it kills harmful bacteria that may be present from the liquid, food, or even air we breathe. But a stomach with low acid is the perfect environment for this bacteria to thrive. This increases the chances of contracting harmful bacteria such as: -C. Difficile -Cholera -Salmonella - and more... Low stomach acid can also increase heartburn and GERD. It’s often thought by the Tums-taking crowd that heartburn is a result of too much stomach acid when it’s actually quite the opposite. Leaky gut has become a world-wide developed country issue, with most of us missing out on the nutrients we take in because our gut cannot process them. Bitters can help with that issue. Digestive bitters are concentrated “bitter” herbs, usually tinctured in alcohol, that improve digestion. The bitter taste signals to the digestive organs to produce the juices necessary for digestion. If you suffer from indigestion, heartburn, bloating, gas, or burp often, you probably would benefit from adding bitters to your diet. Stay away from the antacids, and address the underlying issue with Digest-Support {Digestive Bitters}.

column31: Coming in HOT 🔥 for those who need to hear this ... Hormone imbalances are not the root cause of your health problems. Hormone imbalance is secondary to the primary underlying cause. Conventional Testing: All steroid hormones (female, male and adrenal cortical hormones), and thyroid hormones are bound to carrier proteins in the blood which hold them in an inactive state. Therefore, blood test evaluate potential circulating hormones only. Some free hormone tests, unbound from the protein, through the blood are available, but you must specifically ask for them. Unfortunately, blood/serum tests are not as diagnostically significant in determining abnormal hormone levels. Therefore, this can actually be viewed as an overall disadvantage. Blood tests in general, are more expensive and the free hormone fraction tests are exceedingly more expensive. Protein-bound serum hormones can be affected by several endogenous in exogenous conditions. Xenohormones have the ability to increase levels in bound hormones. Thus, test can look normal or even high through the blood even in the presence of obvious hormonal deficiency symptoms. Excess testosterone can decrease the amount of bound hormones. Blood tests are a late stage detection test. In this unique compartment, the body is obsessed with keeping the bloodstream and homeostasis. Nutrients and other compounds will be taken out of the body tissue and put into the bloodstream to maintain homeostasis. column31: How many people believe that "if it weren't safe or effective, it wouldn't be approved/allowed on the market?" Too many...as this popular cold medicine ingredient shows! The mainstream speaks out against herbs because they say there's "no evidence they work," but...there's no evidence that this drug, which has been on the market for 50 years, works as a cold medicine/decongestant at all! (Who knew they were giant hypocrites?!) Researchers aren't sure about either the efficacy or safety profile of phenylephrine HCL, even though it's in just about every mainstream cold/sinus medicine. It replaced pseudoephedrine because that is now a behind-the-counter drug (due to its use in creating illegal drugs). More recently-completed studies show that phenylephrine doesn't work any better than placebo, and it can have a whole range of side effects, depending on the person and dose. One study says: “Phenylephrine hydrochloride (PE HCl) is widely used for the treatment of nasal congestion, but efficacy at the 10-mg dose is not known for certain.” How is this acceptable? The drug was approved at a time when the only testing done was finding out whether or not the drug was lethal -- if not, it was good to sell! But they have no real idea if it works or what the safety profile for long-term or regular use looks like. This is NOT science. And it's your health that's at risk. Next time you get the sniffles -- stick to natural! column31: In 2016, the Philippine FDA greenlighted a new vaccine against dengue fever for children based on research funded by the vaccine’s manufacturer Sanofi Pasteur. According to the 2014 paper in The Lancet, a study among more than 10,000 children in five Asian countries that showed Dengvaxia worked and had a good safety profile. But, it was too soon to tell. Within weeks of the vaccines rollout, more and more vaccinated children would die from ‘immune enhancement’, also known as Antibody Dependent Enhancement. Dengue fever is a mosquito-born viral disease that occurs in tropical areas that causes flu-like symptoms. The disease is generally mild in younger children (as are most infections) and can be moderate to severe in older kids, adults and people who had a previous infection. The dengue virus is peculiar: A first infection is rarely fatal, but a second one with a different virus type can lead to much more serious disease, because of what is called antibody-dependent enhancement (ADE), in which the immune response to the first virus amplifies the effect of the second type. We saw this same Antibody Dependent Enhancement with prior attempts at coronavirus vaccines, and indeed, could still see this phenomenon with the current vaccines against SARS-Cov-2. In April 2016, the Philippines implemented a $67 million vaccine program with Sanofi Pasteur’s vaccine Dengvaxia. The country began vaccinating 9 and 10 year old school children in highly endemic areas of the country, where at least 70% of 9-year-old children had previously been infected with dengue. The vaccine Dengvaxia consists of an attenuated yellow fever virus that expresses genes of each of the four types of dengue virus. But soon reports of very sick children started coming in. After nearly 830,000 children got the first dose, reports of “enhanced disease” started occurring in recently vaccinated children. For children who had not been exposed to dengue prior to being vaccinated, or who came in contact with dengue for the first time after being vaccinated, the vaccine appeared to worsen the disease and increased the risk.... column31: In the US, antibiotics are still handed out practically like candy -- anyone who presents to a doctor with an infection (even if minor) will often be given a prescription. But antibiotics come with *serious* side effects, for both the individuals and the community. Most antibiotics are prescribed for either respiratory or ear infections, and many are given to children under 2 -- a time when they can do the most damage. (In contrast, most respiratory and ear infections will clear up without antibiotics, and some are fungal or viral and not bacterial in the first place.) Over time, this can lead to increased infections, stomach distress, and even permanently altered metabolism -- which leads to a wide range of chronic issues into adulthood. Antibiotics may even increase the risk of developing some types of *cancer!* Whenever possible, say NO to antibiotics. They should be for serious, life-threatening infections only! But so many people take acid-suppressing drugs that not only fail to address the underlying issue of heartburn and GERD, but can also put them at risk of serious health conditions. Bacterial overgrowth is one of the many issues that having low stomach acid can cause. The low acidity of the stomach fails to eradicate bacteria successfully and this can lead to issues such as: -SIBO -Abdominal pain -Bloating -Burping -Upset stomach -Heartburn -Diarrhea -Gas - and more There are healthier ways to deal with heartburn and upset stomach. You can try natural treatments such as: *Marshmallow Root – Soak marshmallow root in water until it produces a thick gel. This gel is very soothing. column31: I had a feeling there was a delay in what we were seeing when we conduct a #VAERS search, and this confirms it. There are nearly twice as many deaths than what is shown in a search. The second slide are the lot numbers and manufacturers associated with the most deaths so far. The report is: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/vaccines/safety/adverse-events.html VAERS stands for the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System. It is the nation’s early warning system for vaccine safety. Reports can be made by patients, family members, healthcare providers, vaccine manufacturers and others. VAERS is co-managed by CDC and FDA. VAERS staff evaluate reports of adverse events, and follow up with serious adverse reactions such as death. The CDC encourages you to report any clinically significant adverse event that occurs in a patient following a vaccination, even if you are unsure whether a vaccine caused the event. VAERS is underutilized. A 2013 survey found 29% of healthcare providers had never heard of VAERS. The survey found that while 37% of healthcare providers had identified at least one adverse event following immunization, only 17% of those had ever reported to VAERS. VAERS is underreported. An HHS funded Harvard Pilgrim report from 2010 found that fewer than 1% of adverse vaccine events were ever reported to VAERS. VAERS was established in 1990 to fulfill a requirement of the National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act of 1986. By law, vaccine manufacturers are required to report adverse events that come to their attention, and healthcare professionals are required to report adverse events that are considered a contraindication to further doses of vaccine and those specified in the VAERS Table of Reportable Events Following Vaccination. During 2011-2014, VAERS averaged 30,000 US reports annually, with 7% classified as serious. Healthcare professionals submitted 38% of reports, vaccine manufacturers 30% and patients and parents 14%. VAERS is NOT filled with fake reports, just because someone on social media said so. Learn how to generate a report in VAERS: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/what-is-vaers-and-how-to-conduct-a-search/

column31: Polio is a gastrointestinal viral illness spread via the fecal oral route that in 95% of cases is completely asymptomatic, meaning it produces no symptoms. Rarely, in 1% of cases the virus invades the central nervous system, where it targets motor neurons, resulting in flaccid paralysis, which can produce temporary or permanent paralysis. It was unknown why the virus becomes invasive only sometimes, and it was unknown why there was a peak in cases of poliomyelitis in the 1950s. Poliovirus has been around since ancient times, but in the 1940s and 1950s more cases of paralysis emerged–1952 being the highest number of reported cases ever. What happened in the 1940s and 1950s that was different? DDT and Polio In 1945, DDT (dichloro-diphenyl-trichloroethane) came on the US market used both as an agricultural pesticide and as a household insecticide. The organochlorine chemical was used in a variety of both commercial and domestic applications including entire communities, swimming areas, dairies and farms, streets, alleys, and inside the home–even in places that come in contact with infants and food. Even though its negative health effects were known in the 1940s, it would not be banned until 1972, due to Rachel Carson’s phenomenal 1962 book Silent Spring, which inspired John F. Kennedy to form the EPA (Environmental Protection Agency). DDT was even thought to ‘prevent polio’ by killing ‘polio carrying insects’ (even though that’s not how it actually spread) so it was sprayed in large quantities during epidemics, in areas where people, especially children, would play. It’s toxicity to the central nervous system was unknown at the time. DDT is an endocrine disruptor, and a human carcinogen. DDT is a nerve poison in insects and mammals. The peak uses for DDT in these contexts, ie. directly on people, was right during the years of this unusual peak in polio cases. In the late 1940s, DDT was being linked to a new gastrointestinal disease in conjunction with an elusive virus x. The authors of the article published in 1949, write that a new.. column31: Lots of people are interested in using melatonin as a sleep supplement because after all, it's "natural," right? But not so fast.... First, melatonin is a hormone (chemical messenger). If your body is not producing enough, then there's an underlying reason. Simply giving your body the hormone directly doesn't address that underlying issue. Second, the supplements that are on the market are *huge* doses. Studies that have been done on melatonin used much smaller doses (about 0.5 mg in adults), and focused on those with long-term sleep issues. Many people with mild or occasional sleep issues are using doses that are 10 - 20x higher, which is probably not appropriate! But we don't have the studies to know the long-term effects that has. We *do* know that even small doses raise the body's levels to much, much higher than normal levels. Third, side effects. Some people may have none, but several are possible. Fourth, a lot of the supplements on the market have a lot of 'extra' ingredients that are not at all healthy. The bottom line? Melatonin shouldn't be the go-to for sleep issues. It might have a place in serious or ongoing sleep issues, once other needs have been addressed (vitamin/mineral deficiencies and more), and in a very low dose. But for occasional sleeplessness, skip it. Sources: https://n.neurology.org/content/90/15_Supplement/P5.320 https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC6419450/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/26692007:=:https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/26692007/ https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3870602/

column31: Self-love, awareness and personal development in any area of life is about gaining understanding and consistency as much as it is about ...becoming. Flowers, chocolates, candles and perfumes on this Valentines Day. Friends, we are the gatekeepers of our homes. If we are not intentional about reading labels, we may be using toxic items as many will contain an ingredient vaguely called “fragrance.” This catch-all term acts a little bit of a loophole in most cases — because fragrances can be easily replicated with a list of ingredients, they’re considered trade secrets, allowing companies to keep their recipes under lock and key. When it states "fragrance", the kicker is - we don’t know what’s really in these products. According to the Environmental Working Group, the fragrance industry operates with about 3100 stock chemical ingredients, and the average “fragrance” in personal care and household products contains at least 15 of these chemicals that are NOT listed on the label. Also, there are hundreds that can fall into the category of fragrance. And 80% of these chemicals have NEVER been tested for safety. You might be wondering, how is this even allowed to happen? Like I mentioned fragrance acts as a loophole on the FDA's regulation of personal care products. They're considered "trade secret" under the Fair Package and Labeling Act of 1966, which allows companies to NOT list their ingredients so that their formula cannot be replicated easily. Unfortunately, this gives brands the opportunity to add in cost-effective, but toxic, chemicals to their product to make it smell better and last longer. Most common components of “fragrance” contain phthalates — these are known to cause cancer and disrupt hormones. We’re actually looking at significant damage to male’s sperm, affecting fertility, and concentration of musk ketone in breast tissue for women. So what do these fragrances do to the human body? column31: What Is a Vaccine Insert? Every vaccine that is licensed by the FDA comes with a package insert that is 12-20 pages long, which includes everything from ingredients, warnings and precautions, contraindications, adverse reactions gathered from clinical trials and post-marketing surveillance findings. However, healthcare providers are only legally obligated (through Federal law) to provide you with a one-page vaccine information sheet (VIS) before the vaccine is administered. Physicians do not always follow the recommendations of the manufacturers: for example, the Boostrix vaccine insert recommends at least 5 years between repeated Tdap administration, but obstetricians will recommend a pregnant woman to get a Tdap every pregnancy, even if her pregnancy was only a year or two after her previous pregnancy. This recommendation is technically an “off-label” use. According to the Boostrix vaccine insert: “Safety and effectiveness of BOOSTRIX have not been established in pregnant women. (8.1)” Additionally, “BOOSTRIX has not been evaluated for carcinogenic or mutagenic potential, or for impairment of fertility.” Section 13.1 These are some examples of why everyone should read the Vaccine Inserts. column31: Questions to ask your health care provider before consenting for the suggested treatment, that apparently will get us “back to normal”. 1. I understand that several vaccines have been approved for use in Australia. Exactly which coronavirus vaccine are you recommending I should receive? 2. Is the choice of suggested vaccine because that is the one you have been supplied, or that out of all the vaccines available, and based on your medical and scientific research, you believe this to be the best one available for me? 3. Have you looked into my complete medical history before recommending this vaccine to me? 4. I have read documentated adverse reactions on VAERS. Have you considered all possible side effects I might experience, based on my medical history? 5. Have you personally been vaccinated with the same vaccine you are recommending to me? 6. If, as a frontline worker who comes into contact with sick people on a daily basis, you haven’t been vaccinated, why are you recommending that I be vaccinated? 7. Does the vaccine contain MRC-5, or used in the manufacturing process? (aborted fetal cell tissue). 8. Is the vaccine you are recommending to me an mRNA “vaccine”? 9. If so, my understanding is that this is not actually a vaccine, under the accepted definition of a vaccine. Please explain to me why you believe it is safe for me to have an mRNA “vaccine”? 10. What are the risks and long-term effects of mRNA “vaccines”? 11. Is there a possibility of an IATROGENIC REACTION from this vaccine? 12. Can you please list the ingredients of your recommended vaccine, so I can research these for myself before I give you my informed consent? 13. In particular, I am interested to know if any of the following fillers or adjuvants are used, as they are ingredients in other vaccines. - aluminium hydroxide - aluminium phosphate - ammonium sulphate - animal tissues: dog kidney, monkey kidney - chick embryo - fetal bovine serum - formaldehyde - gelatine - glycerol - glutaral - human diploid cells (originating from human aborted fetal tissue) - mercury (thimerosal/thiomersal) - monosodium glutamate (MSG) - neomycin - neomycin sulphate - phenol red indicator - phenoxyethanol (anti-freeze) - potassium diphosphate - potassium monophosphate - polymyxin B - polysorbate 20 - polysorbate 80 - porcine virus (pig) - casein - sorbitol 14. My research indicates that NO vaccine has ever been safety tested with a true double blind placebo test with long term studies. Vaccines are classified as a blood and biological product. Is this true? Instead of being tested with a double-blind placebo test and with a long-term study, a new vaccine is tested against another existing vaccine? In my research I found that at least one of the covid vaccines was tested against a meningococcal vaccine. 15. My understanding is that there is a major difference in the way that my body can process a drug or chemical which is ingested, and one that is injected into my body. My understanding is that anything injected into my body goes straight to my vital organs. Things ingested go through the body’s natural defence system, giving my body the chance to filter out harmful substances to a large extent. I understand that lasting immunity needs to be created using the body’s own natural immune system. Injecting vaccines into my body bypasses that system, so any immunity from a vaccination is only temporary. If my understanding is correct, then it seems to me, that my best strategy is to focus my efforts on strengthening my immune system, rather than choosing to be vaccinated. 16. My research indicates that pharmaceutical companies have been heavily fined for falsifying clinical trials in the past. In December 2020, the Food and Drug Administration granted Pfizer an emergency use authorisation for its COVID-19 vaccine. Has the company that produces the vaccine you are recommending to me, ever been fined for false or misleading advertising, or falsifying their clinical trials? If so, what are the details and why should I be confident in taking their vaccine? As part of my research, I came across this information about Pfizer: https://www.drugwatch.com/ 17. Has the vaccine you are recommending for me been adequately tested on animals before being injected into humans? 18. Have you looked into how the human trials for this recommended vaccine were conducted to determine the level of efficacy of the vaccine? From the research I have done, the high efficacy results claimed by Pfizer and Moderna are based on projections and extrapolations, rather than actual large scale clinical trials. 19. My understanding is that all of the corona virus vaccines have been approved under an emergency approval process before being released for injecting into humans after only about 6 months. Generally it takes many years (usually at least 10yrs) before a new vaccine is released. How can this vaccine possibly be properly tested and safe, with so little testing? Shared.

column31: Sometimes called the detox gene, MTHFR (Methylenetetrahydrofolate reductase) is an enzyme that plays an important role in the Folate Cycle, which plays a central role in cell metabolism and is crucial role for body homeostasis. If you have an MTHFR mutation, it may mean you have an impaired ability to convert folic acid into the more active form of L-methylfolate, which means you could have more unmetabolized folic acid, which can have some untoward effects, such as increase your infant’s risk for autism. The MTHFR gene that codes for this enzyme has the potential to mutate, which can either interfere with the enzyme’s ability to function normally or completely inactivate it. One of the major functions of the MTHFR enzyme is to create a biochemical called Methyl-THF. The “methyl” part of the biochemical will then passed onto another biochemical called homocysteine, which will result in methionine. Essentially, the MTHFR enzyme has tremendous implications on the methionine cycle, which impacts MANY MANY biological functions, including neurological health, cell health, energy health, ability to deal with oxidative stress, and immune health, to name a few things. When the methionine cycle is negatively affected, it is extremely detrimental to the body, and with sufficient environmental stressors, such as toxins or severe infection, may result in brain damage. Read more: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/mthfr-and-pregnancy/ #mthfr #mthfrgenemutation #mthfrpregnancy #mthfrawareness #mthfrc677t #mthfrwarrior #autism #pregnancy #folicacid #folate #methylation #methylfolate

column31: "I had to post this moment I captured this afternoon, hope you enjoy. I stopped by Dollar Tree off Lakeland this afternoon to pick up wrapping paper, and I couldnt help but be drawn to this. This older gentleman very softly said to the lady in the photo, "Mam, would you mind helping me out with something?" As she nodded, "yes, of course, what do you need?" "I need help picking out a birthday card." "Who is it for?", she asked. This is where I started to sniffle. "It's for me, if I wake up tomorrow, I'll be 85." "My wife wanted to get me something, but she's very sick and cannot leave the house, and I want her to know I got a birthday card from her." He continued on to tell stories of how they've been married since they were teenagers, had children, and how she was there for him while he served in military. It was the picture of love you only read about. I felt so privileged to get to hear this conversation. Melted my heart. Hope you all enjoy." Credit: Louisa Lenore McKinney

column31: Everyone should know how to conduct a VAERS search! There is so much disinformation about VAERS. The only way to really set the record straight is if you do your own search, and see it for yourself. To get to CDC Wonder VAERS search: https://wonder.cdc.gov/vaers.html VAERS stands for the Vaccine Adverse Event Reporting System. VAERS is the nation’s early warning system for vaccine safety. VAERS is a passive surveillance system and relies on voluntary reports. Reports can be made by patients, family members, healthcare providers, vaccine manufacturers and others. This does not mean there are fake reports. VAERS is co-managed by CDC and FDA. VAERS staff evaluate reports of adverse events, and follow up with serious adverse reactions such as death. The CDC encourages you to report any clinically significant adverse event that occurs in a patient following a vaccination, even if you are unsure whether a vaccine caused the event. VAERS cannot determine if a vaccine caused an adverse event, but can determine if further investigation is needed. VAERS is underutilized. A 2013 survey found 29% of healthcare providers had never heard of VAERS. The survey found that while 37% of healthcare providers had identified at least one adverse event following immunization, only 17% of those had ever reported to VAERS. VAERS is underreported. An HHS funded Harvard Pilgrim report from 2010 found that fewer than 1% of adverse vaccine events were ever reported to VAERS. VAERS is necessary post licensure surveillance because many possible adverse reactions will not have been detected in pre-licensure clinical trials. VAERS may also contain vaccine errors, for example a vaccine licensed for adults may erroneously be given to an infant. Or a vaccine is given after the expiration date. These reports are also encouraged to be submitted to VAERS. VAERS does NOT have a deadline to report adverse reactions. It is encouraged to submit the report promptly to aid in identification of dangerous lots of vaccines, but there is no deadline. VAERS was established in 1990 to fulfill a requirement of the National Childhood Vaccine Injury Act of 1986. By law, vaccine manufacturers are required to report adverse events that come to their attention, and healthcare professionals are required to report adverse events that are considered a contraindication to further doses of vaccine and those specified in the VAERS Table of Reportable Events Following Vaccination. During 2011-2014, VAERS averaged 30,000 US reports annually, with 7% classified as serious. Healthcare professionals submitted 38% of reports, vaccine manufacturers 30% and patients and parents 14%. VAERS can’t determine causality. But we should not assume all events are merely coincidental. Let’s not forget that a vaccine is an injection. Every injection, especially one that is designed to abnormally stimulate your immune system has risks. VAERS is NOT filled with fake reports, just because someone on social media said so. https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/what-is-vaers-and-how-to-conduct-a-search/

column31: Most trials can only tease out immediate side effects -- soreness, headaches, fevers, etc. Those are fairly easy because they happen quickly and are obvious. Long-term side effects are much harder to tease out. To find out if there is an actual causal relationship, researchers have to look at extremely large groups of people and follow them for several years (one group who received the intervention and one group that didn't, matched for age, sex, health concerns, etc.), and then see if certain diagnoses are more common in the intervention group than the non-intervention group. It's hard to do studies of this scale in the first place. It's *impossible* on interventions (like the new C-v@x) that haven't been around long enough to have studied anything long term. It's also hard to prove, for sure, that any trends seen, especially if they're still "uncommon," are actually, causally related to the intervention. So, those who have financial and emotional incentives to believe in the intervention, at any cost, simply dismiss these long-term effects as coincidence. It's hard to find enough evidence for them, and it's much more mentally comfortable to see them as a coincidence. This, of course, ignores the lived experiences and pleas of those who are unlucky enough to suffer the side effects. We'll see what happens over the next few months....

column31: I woke up this morning to find myself tagged in a post by an old friend. He was more of a friend of a friend back in our university days. So back in 2005. I had been in conversation with another nurse who was saying that i was uneducated, and how I was putting other children at risk for not vaccinating mines. She didn’t like dead or injured children apparently. He had went out of his way and searched for my Registration details, took a screen shot, and posted it. I am not sure how he knows I havent practiced in a few years, but I am still registered. As a RN you have to maintain Continuing Professional Development (CPD) but he probably didn’t know that! I had a dream, a while back now that someone had went out of their way to contact the Nursing Board, re my stance on vaccinations. I am pretty in tune with these kind of things. I don't need to worry about that though, as i have decided i will no longer be registering this year, and letting my registration go! Thats what happens these days, people have nothing better to do with their lives, and if you go against the grain of society you are an outcast. We have a No Jab, No Play and a No Jab, no Pay legislation here in Victoria, which means unvaccinated children cannot attend day care or kindy. It also means we are not entitled to family tax benefit. I would have been back working part time if it wasn’t for these legislations, but there wasnt another option for me, I had to stay at home. People are quick to judge, without knowing the reasoning of why someone may be out of work. Thank goodness i found my tribe last year, now working with a team of people. Within the team there are nurses, chiropractors, people who have influence in the political side of things, parents who have vaccine injured children. All fighting for our medical freedom and bodily autonomy, and raising awareness! Who knows, in the years to come the legislations might be scrapped! It is worth trying, for the next generation of children! This guy took several attempts to get into medical school, he failed 3 or 4 times. Good on him, he continued to pursue his dream and passion to be a doctor. Practising now I believe. I have HUGE respect for nurses and medical doctors. They are highly educated and skilled. If you die, they are the ones you want around! The system however, needs a revolution! He would always have something to say when I had something to post on alternative medicine. Not sure why. Max Gerson, on cancer therapy. Dr Caldwell Esselstyn, on heart disease. T. Colin Campbell, on nutrition and disease. Dr Neal Barnard, on reversing diabetes. I can only hope that he is one one of the better ones, and is able to break free from the Rockefeller Medical system, and stop being a Big Pharma supplier. Treat the root cause of the disease of his patients, rather than merely suppressing the symptoms.

column31: Science Is Unsettling: What About Smallpox? So often people say: “Smallpox is an extremely contagious virus that ripped through populations killing millions for centuries. It wasn’t until a vaccination was invented that it was finally eradicated. How can you not see that?” How do we respond to that? No one is debating whether or not smallpox was a potentially lethal virus, or that humans for centuries were extremely malnourished and suffered miserably with both nutritional deficiency diseases–such as scurvy, rickets, pellagra–and infectious diseases alike; many diseases we don’t have anymore. And it wasn’t because of vaccines. We are debating whether the smallpox vaccine is responsible for smallpox’s apparent disappearance. The assumption that one caused the other merely because there’s a temporal relationship is the cardinal sin of ‘correlation does not imply causation.’ We need more. We need evidence. And we can’t have any evidence to the contrary. Was Smallpox Eradicated By a Vaccine? In order for smallpox to have been completely eradicated by vaccination, we are going to need to unscientifically ignore some information that would invalidate or raise doubts within that argument…for example, we must… Ignore the major improvements to public health that occurred around the turn of last century (I’m talking around 1900), such as installation of sewage disposal systems, water treatment, food safety, organized solid waste disposal, hygiene, clean drinking water, improved nutrition, discovery of antibiotics, improvements in housing which reduced overcrowding, etc. Ignore that smallpox was caused by two viruses, variola major, the strain that had a mortality rate of 5%-20% was being replaced by the much less deadly strain variola minor, whose case fatality rate was below 1%, in many parts of the world, including United States in the late 1890s and introduced into the England from Boston in 1902. Ignore that this less deadly strain became the predominant strain in the US after 1897. Full post: https://circleofmamas.com/health-news/science-is-unsettling-what-about-smallpox/ #smallpox #smallpoxhistory #history #scienceisunsettling

column31: Most cinnamon that you buy is cassia cinnamon, a cheaper form of cinnamon. Cassia cinnamon is strong and “knock off” cinnamon. Ceylon is known as the “true” cinnamon and it has a much milder flavor. It sort of like nutmeg, in a way, but not quite. Studies show that Ceylon cinnamon helps to balance blood sugar in diabetics, and may help to lower blood pressure (and more). For medicinal use, it really is important to choose Ceylon and not cassia, because of the high coumarin levels in cassia which can cause side effects. Ceylon won’t do that.

column31: Mumps, MMR, encephalitis, and autism. This little boy received the MMR vaccine at 14 months of age. Four months after MMR vaccination, he was diagnosed with SCID (Severe Combined Immune Deficiency Syndrome). He was diagnosed with autoimmune haemolysis and developed a persistent H1N1 infection. He received successful Stem Cell Therapy and his immune system improved, but six months after Stem Cell Therapy he started regressing and losing cognitive abilities, motor skills, and language. He developed seizures. His hearing was affected and he developed personality changes and behavioral changes. After multiple hospitalisations, he died at 69 months of age. On autopsy, vaccine-strain mumps virus was found in his brain and this was determined to be the cause of chronic encephalitis - FOUR YEARS AND SEVEN MONTHS AFTER HE WAS VACCINATED. From the report: "Using deep sequencing of fresh brain biopsy material, we identiﬁed the Jeryl Lynn 5 mumps virus (MuVJL5), a component of the measles, mumps, rubella (MMR) vaccine that had been administered to the child before the diagnosis of SCID. Similar to ﬁndings in measles viruses recovered from cases of SSPE, the mumps virus genome from the brain showed evidence of biased hypermutation, particularly in the matrix (M) gene. Comparison with sequence data from the original vaccine batch used to immunise this child identiﬁed the expansion of variants present at low frequency in the vaccine as well as de novo ﬁxed missense substitutions. This case represents the ﬁrst conclusive demonstration of chronic panencephalitis due to mumps virus." Study: https://www.researchgate.net/publication/309362332_Deep_sequencing_reveals_persistence_of_cell-associated_mumps_vaccine_virus_in_chronic_encephalitis

column31: 'Many people sincerely believe that all vaccines are safe, adverse reactions are rare, and no peer-reviewed scientific studies exist showing that vaccines can cause harm. A more reasonable perspective, however, is that while vaccines may contribute toward enhancing immunity against contracting specific diseases, they are also responsible for causing autoimmune disorders and other detrimental long term effects that are rarely disclosed. Primum non nocere is Latin for "First, do no harm", one of the guiding principles of medical care. Yet there is a large body of scientific evidence confirming numerous vaccine safety deficitis that counteract well-publicised benefits. For example, several studies in this book show that mercury and alumimum in vaccines can cause neurological, immunological and developmental harm. Other studies show that childhood vaccines are associated with an increased risk of cancer, allergues, seizures, bleeding disorders, and type 1 diabetes. The peer-reviewed scientific studies in this book also show that.. • The pertussis vaccine caused virulent vaccine-resistant strains of pertussis to emerge. • Chicken pox vaccines reduced cases of chicken pox but increased cases of shingles. • Children have an increased risk of requiring emergency care after receiving MMR. • Vaccinated people can spread disease, making "herd immunity" an unrealistic goal. This book - Miller's Review of Critical Vaccine Studies - provides the other side of the story that is not commonly told. It contains summaries of more than 400 important scientific papers to help parents and researchers enhance their understanding of vaccinations.' Highly recommend this book. Informed consent. Always 🖤

column31: Friends, if you follow my work, you know I talk a lot about environmental toxins and root cause issues and underpinnings affecting our health. This goes for lung health as well. A little bit about me personally ... I had respiratory infections my whole life until about 10 years ago. If you didn't know, I was a "bubble baby". I had every pneumonia, bronchitis, sinus infection, strep throat and chest cold going around and known to man. Plus my entire family were heavy in the house smokers. It wasn't until I changed my environment, read, read. and read some more, researched, researched, listened to podcasts (over and over and over - I do love them!), and took a deep dive and really cleaned things up; my gut, my liver, my gallbladder, my DIET, implementing deep detoxification to help my lymph system perform better, lifting weights, yoga, mindfulness, working on emotions and traumas, getting chemicals OUT of my home and body and using pure oils. That is when the ship REALLY turned around 🚢! Lung dis-eases are some of the most common medical conditions in the world. Tens of millions of people have lung disease in the U.S. alone. Smoking, infections, environmental toxins, metals and pathogens can be at the root of lung dis-eases. Your lungs are part of a complex eliminatory system, expanding and relaxing thousands of times each day to bring in oxygen and send out carbon dioxide. Lung dis-ease can happen when there are problems in any part of this system and other system, as everything is interconnected. Root Cause Issues ... As a Naturopath of 16 + years, I have learned that what is manifesting, is usually secondary to underlying causes. So if you have lung issues developing, please be sure to take a deep dive at what is happening behind the scenes, as everything about your lifestyle, diet, routines, thoughts and emotions and exposures are affecting how and what symptoms are manifesting. According to Chinese medicine, the spleen controls the lung, so always assessing and balancing the spleen will be crucial.
